result.execSummary:
The defendant Tony M. Sharratt was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property (Over $2500) [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(2)(d).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
Restitution to be Joint and several with convicted co-defendants.

$2500.00 cash bail to be applied .

If probation is discharged/revoked with outstanding financial obligations due, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due and/or other collection procedures will be implemented. If revoked and sent to prison, DOC shall withhold 25% of all inmate monies to pay fines/costs/surcharges/restitution with the balance due as a condition of extended supervision/parole.

To pay supervision fees as determined by the DOC.

Counseling as recommended by agent.

Letter to all victims to be forwarded to the Reporter to be published.

To provide DNA Sample and pay surcharge.

timeConds.notes:
Huber, out of county travel, for child care, employment and work search  granted at the discretion of  jail administration. 

Defendant shall complete Jail Check-In packet immediately. Jail staff shall contact the defendant within 72 hours of receiving JOC to set report date, which shall be within 60 days.
To perform 20 hours community service per year of probation.
